The Armenian is colloquial and a bit slangy, so a literal translation sounds weird in English. Breaking it down:

> **հա լավ էսքան խոտ մարդ ըլնի**
> “yeah okay, as long as there are this many ‘grass’ people”

and

> **մի հատ էլ պալիտիկ 🤭😅**
> “and one more politician 🤭😅”

The key word is **խոտ** (“grass/hay”). In Armenian internet slang, calling people “grass” can imply they’re passive, dumb, easily manipulated, or sheep-like — similar to “NPCs,” “bots,” or “mindless masses” in English political slang.

So the commenter is basically mocking the support shown in the video. The implied meaning is something like:

* “Yeah sure, when there are this many sheep, of course you’ll get another politician.”
* “With this many gullible people around, another politician pops up.”
* “Well yeah, if there are this many clueless supporters, no surprise.”

The second line “մի հատ էլ պալիտիկ” is intentionally half-jokey. **պալիտիկ** is a colloquial/russified/slangy form related to “politician/politics” (“политик” influence from Russian). The tone is sarcastic rather than formal.

Overall tone:

* sarcastic
* dismissive toward Pashinyan supporters
* internet-comment style humor
* “people are sheep and politicians exploit them” vibe.

